message: Merged sections about the same topic and removed repetitive comments. Please do not comment unless you have something new to bring
Move to the bottom to reflect timing
Removed puffery (not present on other university pages)
Discussion about "one of the most prestigious in the world" in the introduction

Undid revision 1028189724 by [[Special:Contributions/15|15]] ([[User talk:15|talk]]) Citing subjective sources does not make this article less biased. It needs major cleaning up. The article reads with the intention of promoting Oxbridge over other universities, through subjectivity
Undid revision 1028189793 by [[Special:Contributions/15|15]] ([[User talk:15|talk]]) Undoing claims
Removed non-solid notions from introduction (WP:UNIGUIDE). This has been removed before but was re-added for some reason.
Slightly more clear to use the word "university" as opposed to repetition
Remove [[WP:PUFFERY]]. This is not solid and is biased. See [[WP:UNIGUIDE]].

This article should not be trying to promote features like this with subjective opinions in the opening. It is not proper and influences readers in a biased way. See [[WP:UNIGUIDE]]. This feature is also not unique
Removing more non-solid points that promote bias
"claims to practise" again takes a rather poor tone
Added more information about academic small-group Imperial tutorials
This sort of subjectivity leads to bias and does not meet Wikipedia's standards for editing
[[WP:FIXBIAS]] If this is an article centred around the tutorial system for teaching undergraduate degrees, why does it seek to promote Oxbridge over other universities? That is bias
Removed [[WP:PUFFERY]]. Fiscal information really ought not to be in the introduction
Link to less biased article about tutorials
Edited content to reflect [[WP:UNIGUIDE]] standards. Previous also exhibited [[WP:PUFFERY]]
Ensuring academic fundamentals is not the same as pastoral support
Removed WP:PUFFERY and bias, and added more information. This does not meet Wikipedia's standards for quality of information
This article is incredibly biased. I question the nature of this article
Removed relative terms as it comes across as biased
Specified study was by the UK government
Specified efficacy was against symptomatic COVID-19 infection
Added study from the UK on the vaccine's efficacy. Source provided
Removed unnecessary and unsourced information which should not be in the introduction
Rearrangement to give a clearer picture
This is not a feature unique to Oxbridge. Similar things are present at other universities in the UK and abroad. Also see WP:PUFFERY
Small group teaching exists at other universities in the UK and also in "houses" at other universities, making this not unique
Pfizer vaccine can be stored for 30 days in a standard fridge, the previous information was incorrect and potentially harmful
/* Area characteristics */ University rankings fluctuate year on year and this is not a solid or factual claim to make. Also see WP:PUFFERY and WP:UNIGUIDE.
Wikipedia is not the place for primary data analysis. Regardless, any claims should take a neutral tone
Removed irrelevant detail that should not be part of the introduction
Added more information about academia and reputation similar to the pages of other universities such as Harvard, MIT and Hong Kong. Metrics are included in the sources.
Remove WP:PUFFERY, also see WP:UNIGUIDE. These notions should not be discussed at this point in the article
Removed puffery as notion of prestige is not solid and should not be discussed at this point in the article. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:PUFFERY and Wikipedia:UNIGUIDE
/* Admissions */ Updated average ucas tariff information to more recent admissions. Source provided

Undid revision 1021872631 by [[Special:Contributions/Robminchin|Robminchin]] ([[User talk:Robminchin|talk]]) This is not puffery. It is sourced and evidence-based, and there are similar descriptions on the pages of the University of Sydney and the University of Cambridge for example. Therefore it should be here.
Added sourced description to match the Wikipedia page of the University of Sydney
/* Manufacturing */ restore Covishield vial image at appropriate section
/* Malaysia */ Added CITF press release information on the second batch of the vaccine offered to the public.

Mirorred wikipedia introduction of Oxford University page, which mentions Cambridge being an offshoot of Oxford. In a similar manner, Harvard is mentioned as an offshoot of Cambridge.
